         <note conref="../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/ForRedundantSystemsCheckThatEachSte-0FD805BD"
               otherprops="typeR"
               class="- topic/note ">
            <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For redundant systems: </b> Check that each
step is perform on both units before proceeding to next step.</note>
         <note conref="../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/ForDualSystemsPerformAllTheStepsOnO-0FD807C7"
               otherprops="typeD"
               class="- topic/note ">
            <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For dual systems: </b>Perform all the steps
on one unit, then repeat the complete procedure for the other unit.</note>
         <p class="- topic/p ">
            <ol class="- topic/ol ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the system is in <ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph ">normal operation</ph>
                     <ph platform="SDC" class="- topic/ph ">float charge</ph>.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For systems with a bypass:</b> Open the
bypass mains breaker to disconnect the bypass.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Press both the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ON button</b> and the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">OFF button</b> at
the same time for two seconds. The <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Standby</codeph>.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Open the battery breaker to disconnect the
battery bank.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Open the rectifier mains breaker to turn
off the power supply to the rectifier.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Switch off the source of the DC power supply.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Open the inverter input switch to disconnect
the DC power supply.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Discharge the DC capacitor by keeping the charging/discharge
switch in position 1 until the warning LED turns off.</p>
               </li>
            </ol>After about 30 seconds the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> and all LEDs are off.
The system is turned off and the load is not supplied anymore.</p>
